&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Business Administration, or a related field with a minimum of 5-7 years of experience in scheduling, with a proven track record of managing complex projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required Security Clearance: TS/SCI with Poly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive DoD (preferably NSA) experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be proactive and possesses excellent communication skills to fill this role on a very high visibility program in B7.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in defense, intelligence, or federal projects is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in scheduling software such as Primavera P6, Microsoft Project, or similar tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of project management methodologies (e.g., Agile, Waterfall).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment and manage multiple priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
